Title: Music to Die By
Description: Country Boy White is accused of murdering a man he had an argument with the night of the death. The case turns out to be connected to an old hit-and-run case.
Short Description: Country Boy White is accused of murdering a man he had an argument with.

Title: The Golden Cage
Description: A rich trophy wife gets accused of murder when she tries to leave her powerful controlling husband.
Short Description: A rich trophy wife gets accused of murder.

Title: Death in High Places
Description: Sam Horton dies after his private plane explodes during a flight and the police thinks his daughter, Barbara killed him because of an argument.
Short Description: Sam Horton dies after his private plane explodes during a flight

Title: The Double Negative
Description: Billy Fletcher is accused of murdering the private investigator who blackmailed him but he says he was only following him according to the plan of his father.
Short Description: Billy Fletcher is accused of murdering the private investigator who blackmailed him.

Title: A Life for a Life
Internal Title: Petrocelli -- A Life for a Life
Description: Petrocelli defends a hippie motorcyclist charged with arson after a hotel goes up in flames. After the biker was denied a room, he was heard threatening the manager with burning down the hotel.
Short Description: Petrocelli defends a hippie motorcyclist charged with arson.

Title: Mirror, Mirror on the Wall
Internal Title: Petrocelli -- Mirror, Mirror on the Wall
Description: Jean Carter is said to have killed her friend after an argument with him and some people have seen her after the murder but she insists she hasn't been there.
Short Description: Jean Carter is said to have killed her friend after an argument with him.

Title: An Act of Love
Description: Frank Donato is said to have murdered Anette James, the daughter of a powerful senator and only trust the Italian defense lawyer Tony Petrocelli.
Short Description: Frank Donato is accused of murdering the daughter of a powerful senator.
